description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialist Speech and Language Therapist: Stroke&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£36,070 - £42,712 per annum incl HCAS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;West Middlesex University Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to be part of an energetic and supportive team? We are re-structuring our service and an exciting opportunity has arisen for a dynamic Band 6 therapist. The candidate should be someone with specialist clinical knowledge and skills, who is enthusiastic about service promotion and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team currently consists of 5 Speech &amp; Language Therapists, with 4 additional SLTs based at Chelsea and Westminster Hospital. The adult service offers regular site specific and full department meetings, consistent access to formal and informal supervision and regular peer support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is predominantly based on the stroke unit at West Middlesex University Hospital. We are looking for someone who has experience with videofluoroscopy, but competencies and training will be provided where needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post provides excellent opportunities for on-going personal and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to receiving your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jessica Newman, Clinical Lead for Adult Speech and Language Therapy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;jessica.newman1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07776 317 314&lt;/p&gt;
